    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter suspending Neovim with the :suspend or :stop command, mouse scroll and click events in the terminal emit raw escape sequences (e.g. 0;20;8M32;20;9M) instead of performing normal scrolling or window focus.\nThis does not occur when suspending with `<C-z>`\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nEnvironment: macOS Sequoia 15.4.1, Neovim v0.11.1 installed via Homebrew.\n1. Open any terminal (tested in Ghostty, Kitty, and the default macOS Terminal)\n2. Run: nvim --clean\n3. Enter: \":suspend\"\n4. In the suspended shell, attempt to scroll with the mouse wheel or click in the terminal window.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAfter suspending Neovim with :suspend, mouse scroll and click events should be handled by the terminal (e.g. scrolling the buffer, focusing the window).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim 9.0.2142\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS Sequoia 15.0.1 then updated to macOS Sequoia 15.4.1 \n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.1.4-main+7daabddd\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
